.TH "usb4_port_retimer_nvm_authenticate" 9 "usb4_port_retimer_nvm_authenticate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb4_port_retimer_nvm_authenticate \- Start retimer NVM upgrade
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" usb4_port_retimer_nvm_authenticate
.BI "(struct tb_port *port "  ","
.BI "u8 index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
USB4 port
.IP "index" 12
Retimer index
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
After the new NVM image has been written via \fBusb4_port_retimer_nvm_write\fP
this function can be used to trigger the NVM upgrade process. If
successful the retimer restarts with the new NVM and may not have the
index set so one needs to call \fBusb4_port_enumerate_retimers\fP to
force index to be assigned.
